instance.description:
There are several matters needing attention when you configure the parameters of tunnel-list.
1.The tunnels in tunnel-list must be configured first.
2.A tunnel can only join in one tunnel-list instance.
3.The instances of tunnels joined in a tunnel-list can not be deleted.
4.The loop tunnels are not allowed to join in the tunnel-list instance.
5.The attribute of tunnel joined in tunnel-list cannot be modified as loop. 
6.Master tunnel must be configured before slave tunnels in tunnel-list instance.
7.Master tunnel cannot be modified or deleted when slave tunnel has been configured.
8.The maximum of slave tunnels in a tunnel-list instance is 1023.

instance-id.description: Tunnel-list instance ID, key of the object, value type is unsigned int.

master.description: The configuration parameter of master tunnel.

master-tunnel-id.description: The ID of the tunnel specified as master tunnel.

slaves.description: The configuration info of slave tunnels.

slave.description: The configuration parameter of slave tunnel.

slave-tunnel-id.description: The ID of the tunnel specified as slave tunnel.
